uration annotations and conditions, but this dependency is optional and is not present in the normal target-only compile classpath.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-http-codec:4.1.0-RC1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The module has a runtime implementation dependency on Boot HTTP codecs; tests that exercise WebClientCodecCustomizer need CodecCustomizer on the test compile classpath.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-test:4.1.0-RC1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Spring Boot's own tests for this module use ApplicationContextRunner to exercise auto-configuration behavior, which is the normal focused way to test this kind of module.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-micrometer-metrics:4.1.0-RC1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The WebClient observation auto-configuration is conditional on Boot Micrometer observation properties from this optional module.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image or external service appears necessary. Prefer in-process loopback HTTP tests using JDK HttpServer or WebClient test doubles; no environment variables or system properties are required by the library.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Several Spring Boot 4 module dependencies are optional or runtime-only, so tests that only depend on spring-boot-webclient can silently avoid the primary auto-configuration paths.\",\n    \"The requested version is an RC; local Gradle dependency resolution and native-image verification remain authoritative if module metadata differs from the published POM.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c0414957c32668b016a3ef96d47fc8193ad15a27a02c26f8b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-respons